              corresp="#jeru0177.translation">
            <p>שימי בר עשיה אחוי <supplied reason="undefined">ד</supplied> חנין </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:id="jeru0177.translation"
              corresp="#jeru0177.transcription">
            <p>Shimi, son of Ἁsiya, brother of Hanin</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Battered, worn and reconstructed ossuary has red wash, low feet, and a broken flat lid. Ornamentation, on the chest's front side, consists of a lattice-patterned frame with zigzag borders containing three six-petalled rosettes within zigzag circles. שימי is a contraction of שמאי, both used by a second century CE sage; עשיה is a Biblical name occurring as עשיהו on several pre-Exilic seals, and perhaps identical with the name Ἀσιας in a Roman Jewish epitaph; חנין is a contraction of חנינא, a common name in the period, parallel to חנניה.</p>
         </div>
